JOS – Plateau Women in their bid to commemorate International Women’s Day 2022 have organised a two-day women summit in Jos to brainstorm on issues that affect the development of Women on the Plateau and the way forward. The Women Summit under the platform of “women for women and He for She” discussed among other things, issues affecting women and the need to create change in perception about the issues and proffering of solutions to the challenges. In her address at the event, the state chairperson of the program Mrs Rhoda Jahota Jiwul said women generally are achievers and also the brain behind everything in the world According to her, there is no doubt that women are making the world a better place for all to live in, stressing that international women’s day is a big event to commemorate the cultural, political and socio-economic achievements of women as it draws attention to several issues such as gender inequality reproductive right and violence/ abuse against women She expressed happiness that plateau women are among the women across the globe that have overcome different hurdles and are making their places evident in society. GIZ-SEDIN Representative at the event, Hawa Manklik in her address, charged Plateau women to activities participate in government activities and as well work hard to overcome challenges they face in their quest to have access to Land, gender inequality and other constraints facing them. She called on them to put lobby the government to implement the resolutions that reached the summit. The GIZ- SEDIN Representative wished the women to come up with solutions to the issues of discrimination against women which she said could be achieved with the support of men. POLL In a communique reached by the Women at the end of the summit, it was agreed that there should be deliberate training for leadership and team building for women and capacity building in organizational development. It was also agreed that women should organize themselves into associations and groups to champion the cause and interest of women at the state and national levels.The two days Women Summit in Jos was powered GIZ-SEDIN Program on the Plateau.